overview.what:
Three keywords that control loop flow:

break exits the loop immediately — the remaining items are never visited:

  for user in users:
      if user['role'] == 'admin':
          admin = user
          break

continue skips the rest of the current iteration and jumps to the next item:

  for record in records:
      if record['status'] == 'deleted':
          continue
      process(record)

The else clause on a loop runs ONLY when the loop completes without hitting a break. It does NOT run if break was used:

  for route in routes:
      if route == '/admin':
          print('found')
          break
  else:
      print('/admin not registered')

The loop else is the correct way to express 'search completed with no match found' — no flag variable required.

practice_tasks.solution:
def first_active(users):
    for user in users:
        if user['status'] == 'active':
            found = user
            break
    else:
        found = None
    return found

users = [
    {'name': 'alice', 'status': 'inactive'},
    {'name': 'bob', 'status': 'active'},
    {'name': 'carol', 'status': 'active'},
]
print(first_active(users))
print(first_active([{'name': 'dan', 'status': 'inactive'}]))

